named-color.description: CSS 数据类型 <named-color> 为颜色名——如: red、blue、black 或 lightseagreen。

hex-color.description: CSS 数据类型 <hex-color> 为描述 sRGB 颜色的十六进制颜色语法的记号，此记号将颜色的主分量（红、绿、蓝）及其透明度写为十六进制数。如: #FFFFFF(白色)

values.name: rgb
values.description: 根据红色、绿色和蓝色值创建颜色。

values.name: rgba
values.description: 根据红色、绿色、蓝色和 alpha 值创建颜色。

values.name: rgb relative
values.description: 根据另一个颜色的红色、绿色和蓝色值创建颜色。

values.name: hsl
values.description: 根据色调、饱和度和亮度值创建颜色。

values.name: hsla
values.description: 根据色调、饱和度、亮度和 alpha 值创建颜色。

values.name: hsl relative
values.description: 根据另一个颜色的色调、饱和度和亮度值创建颜色。

values.name: hwb
values.description: 根据色调、白色和黑色值创建颜色。

values.name: hwb relative
values.description: 根据另一个颜色的色调、白色和黑色值创建颜色。

values.name: lab
values.description: 根据亮度、a 和 b 值创建颜色。

values.name: lab relative
values.description: 根据另一个颜色的亮度、a 和 b 值创建颜色。

values.name: oklab
values.description: 根据亮度、a 和 b 值创建颜色。

values.name: oklab relative
values.description: 根据另一个颜色的亮度、a 和 b 值创建颜色。

values.name: lch
values.description: 根据亮度、色度和色调值创建颜色。

values.name: lch relative
values.description: 根据另一个颜色的亮度、色度和色调值创建颜色。

values.name: oklch
values.description: 根据亮度、色度和色调值创建颜色。

values.name: oklch relative
values.description: 根据另一个颜色的亮度、色度和色调值创建颜色。

values.name: color
values.description: 在特定色彩空间中，根据红色、绿色和蓝色值创建颜色。

values.name: color relative
values.description: 在特定色彩空间中，根据另一个颜色的红色、绿色和蓝色值创建颜色。

values.name: color-mix
values.description: 在矩形色彩空间中混合两种颜色。

values.name: color-mix hue
values.description: 在极坐标色彩空间中混合两种颜色。

values.name: currentColor
values.description: 'color' 属性的值。'currentColor' 关键字的计算值是 'color' 属性的计算值。如果 'currentColor' 关键字设置在 'color' 属性本身上，则在解析时会将其视为 'color:inherit'。

values.name: transparent
values.description: 完全透明。这个关键字可以被认为是 rgba(0,0,0,0) 的简写，这是它的计算值。

values.name: bottom
values.description: Computes to ‘100%’ for the vertical position if one or two values are given, otherwise specifies the bottom edge as the origin for the next offset.

values.name: center
values.description: Computes to ‘50%’ (‘left 50%’) for the horizontal position if the horizontal position is not otherwise specified, or ‘50%’ (‘top 50%’) for the vertical position if it is.

values.name: left
values.description: Computes to ‘0%’ for the horizontal position if one or two values are given, otherwise specifies the left edge as the origin for the next offset.

values.name: right
values.description: Computes to ‘100%’ for the horizontal position if one or two values are given, otherwise specifies the right edge as the origin for the next offset.

values.name: top
values.description: Computes to ‘0%’ for the vertical position if one or two values are given, otherwise specifies the top edge as the origin for the next offset.

values.name: no-repeat
values.description: Placed once and not repeated in this direction.

values.name: repeat
values.description: Repeated in this direction as often as needed to cover the background painting area.

values.name: round
values.description: Repeated as often as will fit within the background positioning area. If it doesn’t fit a whole number of times, it is rescaled so that it does.

values.name: space
values.description: Repeated as often as will fit within the background positioning area without being clipped and then the images are spaced out to fill the area.

values.name: double
values.description: Two parallel solid lines with some space between them.

values.name: groove
values.description: Looks as if it were carved in the canvas.

values.name: hidden
values.description: Same as ‘none’, but has different behavior in the border conflict resolution rules for border-collapsed tables.

values.name: inset
values.description: Looks as if the content on the inside of the border is sunken into the canvas.

values.name: none
values.description: No border. Color and width are ignored.

values.name: outset
values.description: Looks as if the content on the inside of the border is coming out of the canvas.

values.name: ridge
values.description: Looks as if it were coming out of the canvas.

values.name: border-box
values.description: The background is painted within (clipped to) the border box.

values.name: content-box
values.description: The background is painted within (clipped to) the content box.

values.name: padding-box
values.description: The background is painted within (clipped to) the padding box.

values.name: margin-box
values.description: Uses the margin box as reference box.

values.name: fill-box
values.description: Uses the object bounding box as reference box.

values.name: stroke-box
values.description: Uses the stroke bounding box as reference box.

values.name: view-box
values.description: Uses the nearest SVG viewport as reference box.

values.name: initial
values.description: Represents the value specified as the property’s initial value.

values.name: inherit
values.description: Represents the computed value of the property on the element’s parent.

values.name: unset
values.description: Acts as either `inherit` or `initial`, depending on whether the property is inherited or not.

values.name: var()
values.description: Evaluates the value of a custom variable.

values.name: calc()
values.description: Evaluates an mathematical expression. The following operators can be used: + - * /.

values.name: url()
values.description: Reference an image file by URL

values.name: -webkit-image-set()
values.description: Provide multiple resolutions. Remember to use unprefixed image-set() in addition.

values.name: image-set()
values.description: Provide multiple resolutions of an image and const the UA decide which is most appropriate in a given situation.

values.name: -moz-element()
values.description: Use an element in the document as an image. Remember to use unprefixed element() in addition.

values.name: element()
values.description: Use an element in the document as an image.

values.name: cross-fade()
values.description: Indicates the two images to be combined and how far along in the transition the combination is.

values.name: -webkit-gradient()
values.description: Deprecated. Use modern linear-gradient() or radial-gradient() instead.

values.name: -webkit-linear-gradient()
values.description: Linear gradient. Remember to use unprefixed version in addition.

values.name: -moz-linear-gradient()
values.description: Linear gradient. Remember to use unprefixed version in addition.

values.name: -o-linear-gradient()
values.description: Linear gradient. Remember to use unprefixed version in addition.

values.name: linear-gradient()
values.description: A linear gradient is created by specifying a straight gradient line, and then several colors placed along that line.

values.name: -webkit-repeating-linear-gradient()
values.description: Repeating Linear gradient. Remember to use unprefixed version in addition.

values.name: -moz-repeating-linear-gradient()
values.description: Repeating Linear gradient. Remember to use unprefixed version in addition.

values.name: -o-repeating-linear-gradient()
values.description: Repeating Linear gradient. Remember to use unprefixed version in addition.

values.name: repeating-linear-gradient()
values.description: Same as linear-gradient, except the color-stops are repeated infinitely in both directions, with their positions shifted by multiples of the difference between the last specified color-stop’s position and the first specified color-stop’s position.

values.name: -webkit-radial-gradient()
values.description: Radial gradient. Remember to use unprefixed version in addition.

values.name: -moz-radial-gradient()
values.description: Radial gradient. Remember to use unprefixed version in addition.

values.name: radial-gradient()
values.description: Colors emerge from a single point and smoothly spread outward in a circular or elliptical shape.

values.name: -webkit-repeating-radial-gradient()
values.description: Repeating radial gradient. Remember to use unprefixed version in addition.

values.name: -moz-repeating-radial-gradient()
values.description: Repeating radial gradient. Remember to use unprefixed version in addition.

values.name: repeating-radial-gradient()
values.description: Same as radial-gradient, except the color-stops are repeated infinitely in both directions, with their positions shifted by multiples of the difference between the last specified color-stop’s position and the first specified color-stop’s position.

values.name: steps()
values.description: The first parameter specifies the number of intervals in the function. The second parameter, which is optional, is either the value “start” or “end”.

values.name: cubic-bezier()
values.description: Specifies a cubic-bezier curve. The four values specify points P1 and P2  of the curve as (x1, y1, x2, y2).
